         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Leschenault ¶ Aug 3rd 1881 ¶ Baron F. von Mueller. ¶ Adelaide ¶ Dear Sir....</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">81.08.03</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Forster Johnston</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M1, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS found with a specimen of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Asplenium furcatum</seg> (MEL 114819). MS annotation by M: 'Answ 29/8/81'. Letter not found.</p>
               </note>Leschenault<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">WA.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Aug 3rd 1881</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron F. von Mueller.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Adelaide<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">sic</seg>. The letter evidently reached M, notwithstanding its being mis-addressed.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Sir.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Lately while visiting my cattle run<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">On the Preston River, east of Bunbury, WA (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">South western times</seg> (Bunbury), 22 May 1835, p. 3).</p>
               </note> I went to a most extraordinary formation of granite boulder rocks to the extent of 2 or 3 acres &amp; growing on these rocks, I gathered some very beautiful Ferns which were quite new to me, &amp; Mr Clifton<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">In 1874 Forster Johnston had married a daughter of Robert Williams Clifton, and before his marriage had managed the Leschenault property of her uncle, W. Pearce Clifton (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">South western times</seg> (Bunbury), 22 May 1835, p. 3). Many Clifton relatives resided in the area of Australind and Leschenault, and it is not possible to positively identify the Clifton who urged that M receive the specimen.</p>
               </note> has begged me to send them to you as he thinks they would interest you, so that I am forwarding them by the mail, but I gathered one or two other kinds more beautiful than the enclosed, but they were so delicate that they were too much dried up before I could press them so that they were spoilt, but I shall be going out there before long again &amp; shall make a point of going to the same spot again when I shall get a large quantity &amp; if there is anything new &amp; you would like to have any more I shall be very happy to forward them to you</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">I remain</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Yours Truly</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J. Forster Johnston</p>
         </div>
